    <text id="A8513T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Robert Cowan requests that he be repaid, because he "never was harder run for
                    money" than at that time.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1857-11-18"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 18/57</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Enclosed you have statement of your <abbr expan="account">act</abbr> showing
                        <abbr expan="amount">amot.</abbr> due me this date of $68 54/100.</p>

                <p> I never was harder run for money than I am at this time.-- A note of mine from
                        <abbr expan="Philadelphia">Philda.</abbr> will fall due in bank in a few
                    days &amp; I lack considerably of the <abbr expan="amount">amot.</abbr> to
                    pay it with.</p>

                <p>Now if you can let me have the above <abbr expan="amount">amot.</abbr>, you will
                    confer a great favor on</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="Robert">Robt.</abbr> Cowan</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
